Dialogue: 9,0:02:27.50,0:02:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:29.30,0:02:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did Sekitani Jun's funeral go?
Dialogue: 9,0:02:33.29,0:02:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went off without a hitch.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:35.34,0:02:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:44.18,0:02:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 9,0:02:45.92,0:02:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing... just...
Dialogue: 9,0:02:49.87,0:02:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san...
Dialogue: 9,0:02:51.52,0:02:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to light some incense for my uncle?
Dialogue: 9,0:02:56.64,0:02:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 9,0:02:57.69,0:02:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:59.01,0:03:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking of visiting my uncle's grave soon.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:04.42,0:03:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you... come with me?{A date to a graveyard. Very romantic.}
Dialogue: 9,0:03:13.62,0:03:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:15.15,0:03:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:17.74,0:03:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call you when I plan to go, then.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:20.51,0:03:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:24.70,0:03:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle's case included, you always solve mysteries so well.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:30.46,0:03:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really amazing.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:33.48,0:03:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind if you call me lucky,
Dialogue: 9,0:03:37.53,0:03:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but please don't call me amazing.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:41.95,0:03:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're so modest, Oreki-san!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:45.42,0:03:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She seriously doesn't get it.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:48.24,0:03:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, the ancients said some wise words.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:52.45,0:03:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?
Dialogue: 9,0:03:53.46,0:03:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Theory and hot patches will stick to anything."
Dialogue: 9,0:03:58.75,0:04:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The saying actually goes, "Theory and ointment will stick to anything."
Dialogue: 9,0:04:04.72,0:04:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that it?
Dialogue: 9,0:04:06.65,0:04:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you can come up with a theory for anything.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:10.21,0:04:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright then.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:11.70,0:04:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say that the reason you solved all those cases wasn't talent, but luck.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:18.90,0:04:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then wouldn't you call the ability to reason out theories based on clues a talent in itself?
Dialogue: 9,0:04:26.99,0:04:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying I'm a master at making theories?
Dialogue: 9,0:04:29.24,0:04:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you?
Dialogue: 9,0:04:30.58,0:04:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:31.95,0:04:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how I came up with those theories, myself.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:37.25,0:04:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because you've never taken a close look at yourself.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:45.10,0:04:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she's right about that...
Dialogue: 9,0:04:50.41,0:04:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about this, Chitanda?
Dialogue: 9,0:04:51.94,0:04:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come up with some sort of situation.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:53.89,0:04:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you that you can make up a theory for anything.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:58.86,0:05:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds fun!
Dialogue: 9,0:05:02.19,0:05:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a perfect opportunity.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:03.79,0:05:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show her that she can't trust me to solve everything.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:06.35,0:05:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we go with then?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:12.82,0:05:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}Anyone who on October 31st, shopped at Koubundou in front \Nof the station, report to Shibazaki in the staff room immediately.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:25.35,0:05:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that about?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:27.18,0:05:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:30.68,0:05:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's use the announcement just now!
Dialogue: 9,0:05:33.12,0:05:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come up with a theory regarding what that announcement just now was about!
Dialogue: 9,0:05:39.52,0:05:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:40.56,0:05:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accept your challenge.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:47.70,0:05:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:51.91,0:05:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a scary memory, as always.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:56.00,0:05:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.12,0:05:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 9,0:05:59.12,0:06:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}"Anyone who on October 31st, shopped at Koubundou in front \Nof the station, report to Shibazaki in the staff room immediately."
Dialogue: 9,0:06:09.30,0:06:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I need to know what everything means.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:12.02,0:06:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what "Koubundou" is?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:14.18,0:06:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's a small stationery store in front of the station.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:20.44,0:06:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's run by an elderly couple.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:23.31,0:06:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've gone there once before.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:25.30,0:06:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of store is it?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:26.75,0:06:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a normal store.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:29.15,0:06:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,North Elementary is right by it, so it carries everything an elementary schooler would need.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:35.03,0:06:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not a place a high schooler would usually go.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:38.62,0:06:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could say that.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:41.59,0:06:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Shibazaki a teacher here?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:43.72,0:06:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki-sensei is the head teacher.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:47.48,0:06:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you always been bad with names?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:50.76,0:06:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shush.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:55.00,0:06:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I don't have to do it, I won't.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:57.91,0:07:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I have to do it, make it quick" is my motto,
Dialogue: 9,0:07:03.29,0:07:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but this is an important contest.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:05.94,0:07:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll need to put some energy into this.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:09.85,0:07:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First...
Dialogue: 9,0:07:10.70,0:07:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:11.70,0:07:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We know that Shibazaki is trying to call a student.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:14.84,0:07:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I can see that too.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:17.99,0:07:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call this person "Student X".
Dialogue: 9,0:07:26.00,0:07:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This feels like a real investigation!
Dialogue: 9,0:07:34.29,0:07:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you have a seat?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:36.16,0:07:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 9,0:07:44.75,0:07:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we don't know if "Student X" \Nis singular or multiple students.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:53.57,0:07:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki may intend to give this student "educational guidance".
Dialogue: 9,0:07:59.54,0:08:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he's going to scold them for some reason.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:03.45,0:08:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:05.29,0:08:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because a student will only get called to the staff room for something bad...
Dialogue: 9,0:08:10.75,0:08:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by my experience.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:14.26,0:08:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san, are you really taking this seriously?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:17.09,0:08:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been this serious since I got into this school.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:20.52,0:08:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might be more serious now than I've ever been before.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:24.69,0:08:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}If he wanted to commend them, he wouldn't use vague words \Nlike "anyone" or "shopped at Koubundou in front of the station".
Dialogue: 9,0:08:32.38,0:08:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd be more specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.57,0:08:40.29,micho,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn@Iwata Mincho Old Pro-Fate B\blur0.5\c&H3B5141&}{\blur0.5\fs40\pos(208,652.4)\c&HF9E8F8&\b1}Staff Room{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:08:34.07,0:08:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way he worded it, anyone who did know would be too scared to go.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:38.41,0:08:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 9,0:08:40.29,0:08:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And whatever this is, it's urgent.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.15,0:08:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did say "immediately".
Dialogue: 9,0:08:44.75,0:08:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, they always say that when they call someone.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:47.20,0:08:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:48.68,0:08:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This announcement wasn't done in the standard format, so we know that they're in a rush.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:53.87,0:08:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The standard format?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:55.72,0:09:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say you wanted to call me to Classroom 1-A.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:00.95,0:09:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How would you say it?
Dialogue: 9,0:09:01.71,0:09:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 9,0:09:04.06,0:09:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like this:
Dialogue: 9,0:09:05.87,0:09:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki Houtarou-san from Class 1-B, please see Chitanda Eru in Classroom 1-A immediately.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:13.10,0:09:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it?
Dialogue: 9,0:09:14.69,0:09:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try remembering how other announcements go.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:19.98,0:09:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say it like this:
Dialogue: 9,0:09:21.87,0:09:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda Eru from Class 1-A, please see Oreki Houtarou in Classroom 1-B immediately.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:28.53,0:09:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat: Chitanda Eru in Class 1-A, please see Oreki Houtarou in Classroom 1-B immediately.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:36.47,0:09:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter if it's a school announcement.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:38.12,0:09:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most announcements like that are repeated twice.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:41.68,0:09:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this announcement was only read once.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:45.59,0:09:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can say it's because they're in a rush.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:51.12,0:09:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And not just any rush.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:53.53,0:09:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 9,0:09:55.26,0:09:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because this announcement was made after school.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:00.42,0:10:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san, please don't shortcut through the explanations.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:04.34,0:10:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shortcut"...
Dialogue: 9,0:10:05.43,0:10:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a lovely word!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:06.91,0:10:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:10.80,0:10:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that make sense?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:12.22,0:10:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be more effective if they did it tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:28.52,micho,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur4\p1\c&H9DDF97&\pos(168.545,97.455)}m 124 64 l 122 147 124 152 128 157 452 156 457 153 459 148 458 65 453 63 449 63 447 63 272 61
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:18.68,micho,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\fs60\b1\pos(292.622,138.889)}{\fn@Iwata Mincho Old Pro-Fate B\blur0.8\c&H3B5141&}During School{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:10:16.53,0:10:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama High has a lot of clubs, but there are plenty of people who go straight home after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.55,0:10:24.93,micho,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn@Iwata Mincho Old Pro-Fate B\blur0.8\c&H3B5141&\pos(280.622,138.889)}{\fad(100,100)\fs60\b1\pos(287.289,137.556)}After School
Dialogue: 9,0:10:22.30,0:10:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they still made the announcement after school, because the reason behind it occurred after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.81,0:10:25.93,micho,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn@Iwata Mincho Old Pro-Fate B\blur0.8\c&H3B5141&}{\fad(100,100)\fs60\b1\pos(287.289,137.556)}Night
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:27.27,micho,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn@Iwata Mincho Old Pro-Fate B\blur0.8\c&H3B5141&\pos(291.733,137.556)}{\fad(100,100)\fs60\b1\pos(287.289,137.556)}Going to School
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.14,0:10:28.52,micho,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn@Iwata Mincho Old Pro-Fate B\blur0.8\c&H3B5141&}{\fad(100,0)\fs60\b1\pos(287.289,137.556)}SHL
Dialogue: 9,0:10:28.89,0:10:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, it's so important that they can't wait for tomorrow to do it.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:33.50,0:10:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki made the announcement, betting on the possibility that X hasn't gone home yet.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:40.05,0:10:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san, doesn't this smell fishy to you?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:43.75,0:10:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:44.70,0:10:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, why do we say things smell "fishy"?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:47.65,0:10:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:49.75,0:10:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next deduction.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:51.77,0:10:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki didn't want to make public whatever he wants to talk to Student X about.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:56.51,0:11:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know if that's only for now, or if it'll never be publicly known.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:00.52,0:11:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he didn't say why X was called out?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:04.81,0:11:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is that, but it's pretty clear from the announcement.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:11.07,0:11:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:12.83,0:11:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki is the head teacher.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:14.86,0:11:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Educational guidance" is the school counselor's job.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:18.30,0:11:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:19.37,0:11:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usually it's Morishita-sensei who makes those kinds of announcements.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:22.03,0:11:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the Counseling Room?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:24.20,0:11:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second floor of the main building.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:26.62,0:11:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Head Teacher Shibazaki called the student to the Staff Room.
