Dialogue: 9,0:14:02.99,0:14:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a bad theory, given the little time she had, but...
Dialogue: 9,0:14:06.49,0:14:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides theft, none of the others are possible.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:09.89,0:14:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:11.55,0:14:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}If the investigators were looking someone with particular \Ncharacteristics, they would have included that in the announcement.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:18.06,0:14:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Anyone who shopped at Koubundou" is far too vague if that were the case.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:23.22,0:14:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 9,0:14:24.93,0:14:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident occurred at Koubundou, so we can assume that X appeared to be shopping.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:35.52,0:14:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that announcement a message to the culprit to turn themselves in?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:39.05,0:14:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't feel quite right.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:42.45,0:14:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Theory:
Dialogue: 9,0:14:44.18,0:14:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The investigator doesn't know anything about X.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:47.85,0:14:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he believes X will show themselves after the announcement.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:50.97,0:14:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:52.58,0:14:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were the culprit and heard that announcement...
Dialogue: 9,0:14:59.00,0:15:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who on October 31st, shopped at Koubundou in front of the station,
Dialogue: 9,0:15:04.25,0:15:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,report to Shibazaki in the staff room immediately.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:06.85,0:15:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten seconds left!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:08.47,0:15:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:09.94,0:15:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The investigator still doesn't know I did it!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:13.65,0:15:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might be able to get away with it at this rate!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:20.04,0:15:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of circumstances would make them turn themselves in after hearing that?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:24.96,0:15:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remorse over their crime?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:27.10,0:15:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, they would already have done so in that case.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:29.44,0:15:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The announcement wouldn't be related.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:38.57,0:15:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:40.23,0:15:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put aside the question of what the crime was for now.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:43.66,0:15:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's assume X regretted whatever they did, and then apologized for what they did.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:49.36,0:15:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a letter.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:51.05,0:15:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a letter?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:52.45,0:15:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, what's the date today?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:55.47,0:15:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,November 1st.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:57.76,0:16:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means October 31st was yesterday.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:01.55,0:16:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}Why didn't Shibazaki say "yesterday, at Koubundou" instead?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:06.73,0:16:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, that does seem odd.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:09.90,0:16:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he say "October 31st" rather than "yesterday"?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:14.36,0:16:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he had something in front of him that said "October 31st".
Dialogue: 9,0:16:18.79,0:16:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was simply reading right off it.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:21.03,0:16:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a report, or a note?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:22.96,0:16:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:23.86,0:16:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the investigator know that X is involved, yet know nothing about them?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:30.11,0:16:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they believe X would show up if they made that announcement?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:33.54,0:16:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking a step back, why would they think X regrets what they did?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:37.69,0:16:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because X wrote a letter to Koubundou apologizing for what they did.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:41.19,0:16:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like this:
Dialogue: 9,0:16:43.72,0:16:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm really sorry."
Dialogue: 9,0:16:45.49,0:16:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"On October 31st I shopped at your store, but I committed a crime."
Dialogue: 9,0:16:50.63,0:16:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll repay the damages, so please accept this and that."
Dialogue: 9,0:16:54.65,0:16:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Koubundou owners took that letter to the police.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:58.61,0:17:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police, or some similar investigative group, came to Kamiyama High with the letter.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:04.22,0:17:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This happened not long ago.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:05.64,0:17:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then Shibazaki, in a hurry, made the \Nannouncement while reading off the letter.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:12.01,0:17:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 9,0:17:13.25,0:17:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to your theory, X-san wanted to apologize to Koubundou,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.42,0:17:18.43,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.9\fs40\fnMontara Gothic\c&HFFF3FF&\b0\pos(295.686,218.028)\frz1.713} Koubundou
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.68,0:17:18.43,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.9\fs40\fnMontara Gothic\c&H4A4B1D&\b0\frz\pos(1015.77,100.889)}Apology
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.93,0:17:18.43,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.9\fs40\fnMontara Gothic\c&H4A4B1D&\b0\frz\pos(1065,279.6)}Compensation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.68,0:17:18.43,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.9\fs40\fnMontara Gothic\c&H4A4B1D&\b0\frz\pos(249.2,629.6)}Acceptance
Dialogue: 9,0:17:18.55,0:17:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but didn't want to have the police involved, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:23.81,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.9\fs40\fnMontara Gothic\c&HFFF3FF&\b0\pos(284.486,278.828)} {purple building on left - this stays on screen for a while}Koubundou
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:23.81,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.9\fs40\fnMontara Gothic\c&H52451F&\b0\pos(1036.49,86.829)}Confession
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.43,0:17:23.81,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.9\fs40\fnMontara Gothic\c&H52451F&\b0\pos(244.49,621.496)}Arrest
Dialogue: 9,0:17:22.66,0:17:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that, yeah.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:23.81,0:17:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that were the case, they wouldn't have admitted that they were a Kamiyama High student in their letter.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:29.94,0:17:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why did the police know to come here?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:35.10,0:17:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say the police asked the owners if they might have any idea who did it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:40.49,0:17:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'd likely answer that it was probably a Kamiyama High student.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:43.54,0:17:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it'd be obvious if X were wearing their uniform.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:45.71,0:17:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 9,0:17:46.94,0:17:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if X had done anything conspicuous at the time, they'd naturally recall it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:51.76,0:17:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything conspicuous?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:53.21,0:17:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This part may be the key to figuring out exactly what crime X committed.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:58.87,0:18:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X did something to make themselves stand out.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:00.92,0:18:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that in itself wasn't a crime.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:04.29,0:18:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They then committed the crime.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:06.13,0:18:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was something that the owners wouldn't have immediately noticed if not for the letter.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:11.95,0:18:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X regretted what they did.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:14.82,0:18:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And whatever they did was enough to quickly get the attention of the investigators.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:19.34,0:18:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The crime was likely more than simple theft.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:23.43,0:18:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 9,0:18:31.20,0:18:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Caught their attention...
Dialogue: 9,0:18:33.85,0:18:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Broke the law shopping...
Dialogue: 9,0:18:38.11,0:18:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Koubundou carries equipment for elementary schoolers, so they probably don't have any valuables.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:44.60,0:18:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping...
Dialogue: 9,0:18:46.35,0:18:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping...
Dialogue: 9,0:18:47.54,0:18:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:06.81,0:19:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:08.52,0:19:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:09.90,0:19:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X used a counterfeit 10,000 yen bill to pay.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:18.13,0:19:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:20.26,0:19:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But wait...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:21.13,0:19:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:22.90,0:19:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not realistically possible!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:24.74,0:19:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not theoretically possible!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:26.66,0:19:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a failure!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:28.44,0:19:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A catastrophe!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:30.78,0:19:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:34.52,0:19:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:35.86,0:19:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a game, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:42.66,0:19:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:49.44,0:19:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:50.99,0:19:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to take this too seriou—
Dialogue: 9,0:19:52.36,0:19:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:53.85,0:19:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That just isn't possible, Oreki-san.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:56.50,0:19:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:58.78,0:20:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The counterfeit bills that have been used are 10,000 yen bills.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:02.83,0:20:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You concluded that they used a 10,000 yen bill based on that news, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:08.40,0:20:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:09.09,0:20:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no way X-san could have gotten their hands on one.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:12.39,0:20:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or even if they did, they should have been able to exchange it.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:16.31,0:20:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:17.47,0:20:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you think X-san got a hold of the counterfeit bill?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:22.67,0:20:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From an ATM, I assume.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:25.02,0:20:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no easy feat to forge bills good enough to trick an ATM or a bank.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:30.09,0:20:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if they were really that good, there's no way X-san would have noticed.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:34.58,0:20:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe as change...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:38.59,0:20:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly. It couldn't have been given as change.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:42.85,0:20:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apart from commemorative coins, the 10,000 yen bill is the largest bill in our currency.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:47.44,0:20:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get what you're trying to say.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:49.56,0:20:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, the only way they could have gotten one is through a personal connection.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:55.22,0:20:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if their father ran a business and received a fake bill,
Dialogue: 9,0:20:59.91,0:21:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if X had received it as pocket money or something, they would have told their father.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:06.24,0:21:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:07.68,0:21:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or if they got it as payment from a part time job, they still should have been able to exchange it.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:15.14,0:21:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they picked it up?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:16.38,0:21:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too unlikely.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:18.55,0:21:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}I guess someone who's okay with picking up and using a \Ncounterfeit 10,000 yen bill isn't the type to apologize so quickly.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:25.23,0:21:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X probably felt guilty about it from the start.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:29.43,0:21:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we can figure out how they got the counterfeit bill, your theory falls flat.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:39.89,0:21:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A 10,000 yen bill...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:41.95,0:21:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, do you like money?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:45.89,0:21:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose I'd have to say I like rather than hate it.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:50.58,0:21:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you be troubled over throwing away 10,000 yen?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:53.29,0:21:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:54.84,0:21:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But only if it were legitimate money.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:58.79,0:22:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would upset over that, so long as it were their own money.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:03.01,0:22:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason why X felt guilty and yet still used the bill was because it was their own money.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:09.87,0:22:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X got the bill from someone as rightful money owed to them.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:14.48,0:22:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it can't be from a job or pocket money, then there's only one possibility left.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:18.29,0:22:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was given back to them in return for money they had previously lent.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:21.36,0:22:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they felt troubled after realizing that the money they received was fake.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:26.34,0:22:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't really blame them for feeling guilty or wanting to use it at a shop run by an elderly couple.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:34.92,0:22:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in that case, X-san should have been able to exchange it!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:38.96,0:22:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:40.16,0:22:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The counterfeit bill is the Joker in Old Maid.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:42.51,0:22:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one wants to be holding it.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:44.63,0:22:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'd say this situation fits:
Dialogue: 9,0:22:48.66,0:22:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yo X, here's the money I borrowed from you the other day."
Dialogue: 9,0:22:51.47,0:22:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ah, Y-senpai? Thank you very much."
Dialogue: 9,0:22:53.85,0:22:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It was 10,000 yen, right? Here."
Dialogue: 9,0:22:56.56,0:22:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Thank you."
Dialogue: 9,0:22:58.48,0:23:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to their surprise it turned out to be fake.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:03.20,0:23:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X lent the money to Y, who was someone higher in social standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.11,0:23:11.74,pixel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\fad(275,0)\fs28\c&H282218&\pos(666,46)}Standing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.11,0:23:11.74,pixel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\fad(275,0)\fs28\c&H282218&\pos(1175.33,618.667)}{bottom right} Character
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.11,0:23:11.74,pixel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\fad(275,0)\fs28\pos(1056.86,59.143)\c&H282218&}{top right} Social Standing Graph
Dialogue: 9,0:23:07.86,0:23:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they couldn't object when Y gave them back a counterfeit.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:11.74,0:23:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Based on all this, we can say X is only one person.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:15.43,0:23:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}It would be far too unnatural for two or three high schoolers \Ntogether to buy cheap stationary with a 10,000 yen bill.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:25.14,0:23:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is pretty much done now.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:26.54,0:23:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what about Y?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:27.80,0:23:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y got a hold of the counterfeit bill.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:30.26,0:23:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he got it from person "Z" in a similar manner.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:34.14,0:23:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can group everyone above Y into Y as well, and then ask who Y is.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:38.75,0:23:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An unscrupulous shopkeeper? The counterfeiter themselves?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:43.26,0:23:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, it's likely that the police got involved with X in order to trace where the bill came from.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:51.51,0:23:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That concludes my theory.
Dialogue: 9,0:24:01.83,0:24:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I spent all that time talking, and she doesn't even say a word?
Dialogue: 9,0:24:05.21,0:24:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cruel.
Dialogue: 9,0:24:17.10,0:24:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Koubundou's over there, huh?
Dialogue: 9,0:24:20.94,0:24:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}"Anyone who on October 31st, shopped at Koubundou in front \Nof the station, report to Shibazaki in the staff room immediately."
Dialogue: 9,0:24:32.92,0:24:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've certainly come a long way from this...
Dialogue: 9,0:24:36.96,0:24:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 9,0:24:38.72,0:24:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, game over.
Dialogue: 9,0:24:42.95,0:24:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san.
Dialogue: 9,0:24:45.25,0:24:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 9,0:24:46.33,0:24:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you start this game because you wanted to prove something?
Dialogue: 9,0:24:52.40,0:24:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, what was that?
Dialogue: 9,0:24:55.02,0:24:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 9,0:24:59.24,0:25:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san!
Dialogue: 9,0:25:01.84,0:25:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we try to deduce what that was?
Dialogue: 9,0:25:12.03,0:25:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.20,0:25:24.21,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{important!}{big headline} Counterfeit Currency Operation {cuts off} \N22{\fnTimes New Roman}-{\fn}year old gangster member arrested
Dialogue: 9,0:25:25.20,0:25:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we start that game yesterday in order to...
Dialogue: 9,0:25:29.21,0:25:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...reach a wild conclusion?
Dialogue: 9,0:25:35.59,0:25:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Sappy New Year.
